'''Princess Tachibana no Nakatsu''' (? – fl. 539) was [[Empress of Japan]] as the consort of [[Emperor Senka]].<ref> Anston, W.G. (1896). Transactions and Proceedings of The Japan Society, London. Supplement I. Nihongi: Chronicles of Japan from the Earliest Times to A.D. 697. Vol. 1. London: Kegan Paul, Trench, Trüber, & Co.</ref> She gave birth to five children. Tachibana no Nakatsu was the daughter of [[Emperor Ninken]] and [[Princess Kasuga no Ōiratsume]]. She became empress dowager from 539.

'''Tachibana no Naka no Ōkimi''' (橘仲皇女, birth and death dates unknown) was the {{ill|Empress|ja|皇后|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} of {{ill|Emperor Senka|ja|宣化天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}. In the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, she is referred to as Tachibana no Naka no Hime no Mikoto (橘之中比売命). Her father was {{ill|Emperor Ninken|ja|仁賢天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, and her mother was {{ill|Kasuga no Ōiratsume no Ōkimi|ja|春日大娘皇女|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Princess|ja|皇女|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} of {{ill|Emperor Yūryaku|ja|雄略天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}. She was the mother of {{ill|Princess Ishi|ja|石姫皇女|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} (Empress of {{ill|Emperor Kinmei|ja|欽明天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}).

She was enthroned as the Empress of Emperor Senka on {{ill|March 8 (old calendar)|ja|3月8日 (旧暦)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} in the first year of his reign ({{ill|April 14, 536|ja|536年4月14日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}). After her death, she was interred alongside Emperor Senka and their young children in the same {{ill|tomb|ja|陵|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}. The only other Empresses known to have been interred with their Emperors are {{ill|Princess Kasuga no Yamada|ja|春日山田皇女|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} (Empress of {{ill|Emperor Ankan|ja|安閑天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, according to the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, although the current official designation is different) and {{ill|Empress Jitō|ja|持統天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} (Empress of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}).

